<main id="main">
    <hgroup>
        <h1>Hi, I'm Szymon Szadkowski ðŸ‘‹</h1>
        <p>
            The <del>front</del>
            <span class="gradient-text">full-stack</span> developer based in Warsaw
        </p>
    </hgroup>
    <section>
        <h2>Recent work</h2>
        <ul>
            {
                projects.length ? (
                    projects.map((project) => (
                        <li>
                            <a href={project.link} class="gradient-underline">
                                {project.name}
                            </a>
                            {project.description}
                        </li>
                    ))
                ) : (
                    <li>Coming soon...</li>
                )
            }
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>About me</h2>
        <p class="about-para">
            I've always been the kind of person who would be ideal for a job as
            a programmer. I spent a lot of time around computers, was driven to
            complete tasks, and detested being late. I made the decision to only
            work on app development around the beginning of 2020, and just one
            and a half years later - up until that point, I had been freelancing
            - I was able to land a full-time position as a front-end developer.
        </p>
        <a
            href="/about"
            aria-label="Go to about me page"
            class="gradient-underline"
            >Get to know me better
        </a>
    </section>
